  "notes": "The LS1 is the engine that defined the modern LS swap movement. All-aluminum construction sheds roughly 45kg versus iron-block variants, making it highly desirable for weight-sensitive builds. C5 Corvette units use a front-sump oil pan; F-body (Camaro/Firebird) units use a rear-sump pan — pan selection is critical for swap fitment. Uses 24x reluctor wheel and cathedral-port aluminum heads. The F-body LS1 is often preferred for swaps due to the rear-sump pan. ECM is a standalone-friendly 24x unit. Responds extremely well to camshaft, intake, and head upgrades. A core reference engine for all Gen III/IV LS swap culture.",
